data.title: Last year, Kylie Minogue was one of the headline acts at the first-ever Sydney WorldPride. This year, Australia’s favourite homegrown pop...
data.meta_description:
42 likes, 1 comments - concreteplaygroundmelbourne on March 12, 2024: "Last year, Kylie Minogue was one of the headline acts at the first-ever Sydney WorldPride. This year, Australia’s favourite homegrown pop star is leading the bill at another huge event: @splendourinthegrass. ‘Padam Padam’ will echo across North Byron Bay Parklands to warm up winter — and festivalgoers will be spinning around to the music megastar’s three-plus decades of hits.⁠
⁠
Kylie tops a lineup that also boasts Future and Arcade Fire — plus everyone from G Flip, Turnstile, The Presets doing a DJ set, Yeat and Hayden James to Girl in Red, Baby Gravy, Tash Sultana, DJ Seinfeld, Fontaines DC, Royel Otis, Tones and I, and more. Get those gumboots ready — head to the link for all the details.".
